# Configuration
Copy config_example.json to config.json and edit:

cp config_example.json config.json

This will Configure your servers, thresholds, and email settings.

# SSH Setup
Generate SSH key and copy to servers:

ssh-keygen -t ed25519
ssh-copy-id user@server

# Email Setup (Gmail)

Enable 2FA on your Google account
Generate an app-specific password at Google Account Security
Use the app password in config.json

# Usage
Run manually:

python3 health_checker.py config.json

## Example output:
=== System Health Check - 2025-10-07 10:30:00 ===

Checking Web Server (192.168.1.100)...
  ✓ disk: 45%
  ✓ cpu: 23.5%
  ✗ memory: 87%

Alert sent to you@domain.com

# Automation
Add to crontab for hourly checks:

crontab -e

Then, add line: 0 * * * * /usr/bin/python3 /path/to/health_checker.py /path/to/config.json
